before.enText: of a part of the body

data.enText: larger than normal, especially as a result of a disease or an injury
Her eyes were red and swollen from crying.

tr: having an exaggerated sense of self-importance
example: so swollen by victory that he was unfit for normal duty
growing ever more swollen-headed and arbitrary

value.def: If a part of your body is swollen, it is larger and rounder than normal, usually as a result of injury or illness.

example.ex: My eyes were so swollen I could hardly see.
example.tran: 我的眼睛肿得很厉害，几乎看不到东西。

value.def: A swollen river has more water in it and flows faster than normal, usually because of heavy rain.
